msContents.summary: Swedish Legal Manuscript. This late fifteenth-century Swedish manuscript contains Magnus Eriksson's national law as well as two shorter legal texts.

msItem.title: The Church Section of the Provincial Law of Uppland
Upplandslagens kyrkobalk
msItem.incipit:
Vm kyrkio bygning oc vm the dagz wærke nidhe
falla j
msItem.explicit:
oc radhe
halffwe næmpd kyrkia oc krona / oc haffwe then
the fælla wilia

msItem.title: King Magnus Eriksson's National Law of Sweden
Magnus Erikssons Landslag
msItem.incipit:
j Vm swerikis konungx rike hwilkit j sik haffuer
siw biscops døme / oc ix laghmanz døme ower
alt swerike ægher en konungx lik krona
msItem.explicit:
gælde konunghe
løfn oc a xl mark ok thet wari konungx ensak
msItem.bibl: Sweriges gamla Lagar X, pp. 1-371 Ed. 59

msItem.title: The Manorial Court Law
Gårdsretten
msItem.incipit:
Thættæ ær ærlingx høffdinga ok førsta swerikis
ok gøta konungx / stadder ok skipader gardz
rætt ok hans hwsa ok sidhen haffuer han sama ræth allo sino rikis radhe giffuit
msItem.explicit:
ok komi aldre fore wara asyn wthan han nythe særdelis
wara naadh aath

supportDesc.extent: 124. Blank leaves at the beginning and at the end of the book block. 200 143

collation.p: The outer leaves of each quire are of parchment, all the others are of paper.

condition.p: The first and last leaves of the book block have been damaged by damp.

decoNote.p: Chapter headings, initials, running titles and chapter numbers are in red.

binding.p: Brown blind-tooled leather binding. Two metal clasps.

origin.p: The manuscript was written in Sweden at the end of the fifteenth century.

provenance.p:
The manuscript came early into Danish possession. On the front pastedown there is an owner's note from the sixteenth century: Denne bog hør meg
elsebe brade tel. At the bottom of the same page the name of Sten Brahe has been written. On fol. 124r there is an impression of a seal showing the arms of the Rantzau family.

source.p: Catalogued 25.02.2000 by EW-J, AWS and AMH. Amended 13.06.2004 by JA.

custEvent.p: The manuscript was photographed in 1988 and prints were made the following year.

list.item: Black and white prints (Portraits and documentation images of the binding, spine, upper and lower pastedowns, details of damages at the spine and the corners. Openings of fols 1, 7, 15, 21, 29, 63, 124v, including the seal. Detail of impression of seal, the beginning and the fly-leaves).
